arts.ttl: Dino Toppmöller: I would have liked a little more control
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt’s coach praised his young team for playing confidently in a 3-1 win over Holstein Kiel. Meanwhile, Bundesliga debutant’s coach conceded that they deserved to lose.

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt weather late pressure to secure 3-1 victory over Holstein Kiel
arts.sum: Already flying high in the standings, Eintracht Frankfurt consolidated third place with a relatively straightforward win against basement side Holstein Kiel, Hugo Larsson, Tuta, and Can Uzun all on target for the Eagles. Holstein Kiel's goalkeeper Dähne made a penalty save to deny Hugo Ekitiké - Alex Grimm

arts.ttl: No Marmoush, no problem: Frankfurt beats Kiel 3-1 to consolidate 3rd place in Bundesliga
arts.sum: Hugo Ekitiké saw a penalty saved and had a late goal ruled out for offside, but others stepped up to score the goals that showed Frankfurt can live without Egypt forward Omar Marmoush. Eintracht Frankfurt snapped its run of three draws and consolidated third place in the Bundesliga with a 3-1 win over relegation-threatened Holstein Kiel on Sunday.

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt gain top four ground with win vs Kiel
arts.sum: Three goals within the first hour saw hosts Eintracht Frankfurt past relegation-struggling Holstein Kiel, despite a second-half fight from the promoted side on Sunday in the Bundesliga.
